column5: One of the local lads out here decided to get his truck washed on New Year's eve...he was extremely lucky that he was only in 4' of water....the backhoe went in too  They finally got both vehicles out at 8:00PM New Years day.....  ...here's some pics      The backhoe wasn't heavy enough to get the truck out, so they brought the BIG GUN in    The weather is gonna warm up for the next few days....PLAY SAFE!!
Wonder if he had his flotation suit on?
Betcha that cost a pretty penny...  Burt

Reminds me of a story I heard on the radio once: some guys were ice fishing with their lab and decided to use a stick of dynamite to blow a hole in the ice. they threw the dynamite out away from them, the dog being a labrador RETRIEVER goes out and starts to haul it back. They try shooting the dog, he hides under the truck, burns himself on the exhaust, bolts out and BOOM the truck is at the bottom. I thought it was quite improbable but funny none the less.
